<span>“The massacre continues, anger and pain are no longer enough.” This is said by the general secretaries of Uil Sicilia and Uil Trapani, Luisella Lionti and Tommaso Macaddino, who add: "Let the judiciary and forces of order assure justice and truth to the family of the worker who died at work today in Salemi. We, in the meantime, denounce inertias, delays, political measures. If something is not done immediately, if the governments do not face the causes of this massacre that is consumed every day in the yards, in the fields and in the factories, the number of deaths on the job will still grow following a tragic trend that in Sicily is all in a few numbers: 65 victims in 2023, 60 in the previous year. This year, the deaths between January and March were 10 and just in mid-May we approach dangerously at altitude 20. We call for training, controls, prevention. It is not a question of driver's license. The life of a worker is not assessed at points!"</span>
&nbsp;
